# IH35-TMS — ALWAYS READ FIRST (every block, every file edit, every conversation)

This file is auto-loaded by Cursor at the start of every interaction in this repo.

## STEP 1 — Before writing ANY code, read these files in order:

1. `docs/specs/CURSOR-PERMANENT-RULES.md` — the permanent ruleset
2. `docs/specs/IH35_MASTER_BLUEPRINT_v3_FULL.md` — the formal canonical blueprint (read the section relevant to the current block)
3. `docs/specs/IH35_UNIFIED_BLUEPRINT_ADDITIONS.md` — chat-derived additions and refinements
4. `docs/specs/IH35_ARCHITECTURAL_DESIGN.md` — every module, every tab, what each does
5. `docs/approved-screens/<relevant-module>.png` — the approved UI for the module being touched

If guidance conflicts: chat-derived additions WIN over the formal blueprint, and the architectural design WINS over both for tab-count and tab-name questions.

## STEP 2 — RESPOND BEFORE CODING

Before generating any code, respond with this exact format:

```
Spec sources reviewed:
- [list each file actually read]

Approved screens reviewed:
- [list each PNG actually viewed]

Deviations from spec required (with rationale):
- [list any deviation, or write "None"]

NEW SPEC items (in this block but not in either spec source):
- [list, or write "None"]

Proceeding.
```

This response is the audit gate. Code generation does NOT begin without it.

## STEP 3 — LOCKED INVARIANTS (carry into every block)

- `operating_company_id` RLS on every table touched
- All views: `WITH (security_invoker = true)`
- Lockstep INSERT pattern for atomic transactions
- Append-only audit events on every mutation
- Permanent records: void, never delete
- Migrations idempotent (DO + IF NOT EXISTS pattern)
- Cache from `master_data.drivers` NEVER used in render path (Part 4.5.4.2)
- Single-link constraint per WF-012
- Single-factor invariant per WF-017
- Display IDs server-generated, never editable
- Production NEVER serves fake data — env-gate fixture fallbacks
- Primary buttons: "+ Create" or "+ Book" (NEVER "+ New", NEVER "+ Add")

## STEP 4 — POST-PUSH CONFIRMATION

After every commit + push, paste back to Claude (planning):
1. Feature branch head commit hash
2. Diff stat
3. Per the block's PAUSE section, every numbered confirmation requested
4. Confirmation typecheck + build green
5. Confirmation `db:verify:*` PASS (only known pre-existing failures acceptable)
6. Confirmation route registrations updated in `apps/backend/src/index.ts` if new routes added

## STEP 5 — TAB DRIFT IS FORBIDDEN

If your work adds, removes, or renames a sub-nav tab in any module:
- You MUST update `docs/specs/IH35_ARCHITECTURAL_DESIGN.md` in the SAME commit
- The CI gate `npm run verify:arch-design` will FAIL the build if tab counts diverge
- The PR template checklist will block the PR if you didn't check the design-was-reviewed box

If you discover a tab in code that is NOT in the architectural design: STOP. Ask Jorge whether to add it to the design or remove it from code.

## STEP 6 — DO NOT LIST (universal)

- Do NOT modify Phase 1 closed deliverables
- Do NOT serve fake data in production (env-gate fixtures)
- Do NOT delete records (void instead)
- Do NOT skip audit events
- Do NOT inline-write SQL that bypasses RLS
- Do NOT mutate the canonical blueprint MD file (additions go in `IH35_UNIFIED_BLUEPRINT_ADDITIONS.md`)
- Do NOT add a tab without updating `IH35_ARCHITECTURAL_DESIGN.md` in the same commit
- Do NOT use "+ New" or "+ Add" — always "+ Create" or "+ Book"

End of mandatory startup file.
